Edo state governor, Godwin Obaseki, has joined the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). The party, on its Twitter handle, @OfficialPDPNig announced the development Friday afternoon. “Breaking News! The governor of Edo State, H.E. @GovernorObaseki has defected to our great Party, the @OfficialPDPNig. The declaration was made this afternoon at the state Secretariat of our party in Benin city, Edo State. Power to the people. #EdoIsPDP,” the party tweeted. Details later…